About YRF Spy Universe:
YRF Spy Universe is a first of its kind cinematic universe of spy thriller films in India. The first film in the universe, "Ek Tha Tiger", starring Salman Khan and Katrina Kaif was released in 2012, followed by its sequel "Tiger Zinda Hai" in 2017. The third film in the universe, "War" was released in 2019 and starred Hrithik Roshan and Tiger Shroff in pivotal roles. "Pathaan" was the fourth instalment in the Spy Universe franchise which was released in 2023 starring Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone and John Abraham. "Tiger 3", the fifth instalment in the YRF Spy Universe and the third film in the Tiger series, starring Salman Khan, Katrina Kaif and Emraan Hashmi, released in 2023. "War 2" is the sixth film of the YRF Spy Universe franchise and will release on 14 August 2025. The film stars two of the greatest cinematic icons Hrithik Roshan and NTR, with Kiara Advani in the lead and is directed by Ayan Mukerji. ‚ÄúAlpha‚Äù, the seventh instalment in the franchise and Hindi cinema's first female-led YRF Spy Universe film, starring Alia Bhatt and Sharvari, is set to release on 25 December 2025.

snippet.title: The Conjuring: Last Rites | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
Discover why this case ended it all. #TheConjuring: Last Rites - Only in Theaters September 5.

From New Line Cinema comes the ninth entry in the more than $2 billion theatrical Conjuring universe, The Conjuring: Last Rites, directed by franchise veteran Michael Chaves and produced by franchise architects James Wan and Peter Safran.

The Conjuring: Last Rites delivers another thrilling chapter of the iconic Conjuring cinematic universe, based on real events.  Vera Farmiga and Patrick Wilson reunite for one last case as renowned, real-life paranormal investigators Ed and Lorraine Warren in a powerful and spine-chilling addition to the global box office-breaking franchise.

Farmiga and Wilson star alongside Mia Tomlinson and Ben Hardy, who portray Ed and Lorraine‚Äôs daughter Judy Warren and her boyfriend, Tony Spera, as well as Steve Coulter returning as Father Gordon, Rebecca Calder, Elliot Cowan, K√≠la Lord Cassidy, Beau Gadsdon, John Brotherton and Shannon Kook.

Chaves directs from a screenplay by Ian Goldberg & Richard Naing and David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick, story by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick & James Wan, based on characters created by Chad Hayes & Carey W. Hayes.  The executive producers are Michael Clear, Judson Scott, Hans Ritter, David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick, Natalia Safran, John Rickard and Michael Chaves.

Chaves is joined behind the camera by his creative team, including director of photography Eli Born, production designer John Frankish, editors Elliot Greenberg and Gregory Plotkin, visual effects supervisor Scott Edelstein, visual effects producer Eric Bruneau and costume designer Graham Churchyard, with casting by Rose Wicksteed and Sophie Kingston-Smith.  The music supervisor is Ian Broucek and the music is by composer Benjamin Wallfisch.

New Line Cinema Presents The Safran Company / An Atomic Monster Production, The Conjuring: Last Rites.  The film will be released worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures and will be only in theaters and IMAX¬Æ in North America on September 5, 2025, and internationally beginning 3 September 2025.

snippet.description:
Prime Video India Presents
Arabia Kadali Official Trailer
Starring Satyadev, Anandi, Nasser, Raghu Babu, Dalip Tahil, Poonam Bajwa, Prabhavathi, Harsh Roshan, Pratyusha Sadhu, Kota Jayaram, Vamsi Krishna, Bharath Bhatia, Chandra Pratap Thakur, Danish Bhatt, Ravi Varma, Amith Tiwari, Nihar Pandya, Alok Jain
Created by Krish Jagarlamudi
Directed by V V Surya Kumar
Music and Background Score: Vidya Sagar
Produced by :  Y. Rajeev Reddy and J.Sai Babu
Written by : Krish Jagarlamudi and Chintakindi Srinivas Rao

Official Release Date August 08, 2025 on Prime Video India.

A suspenseful drama series that follows a group of fishermen from rival villages who unknowingly cross into international waters and are imprisoned in a foreign jail. Their harrowing journey evolves into a powerful saga of resilience, showcasing an unbreakable will to fight for justice. Will the fishermen make it back home? Can the two villages reunite?

snippet.title: [EN] 2025 PMWC at EWC Grand Finals D1 | PUBG MOBILE WORLD CUP at ESPORTS WORLD CUP
snippet.description:
üèÜ GRAND FINALS DAY 1 | AUGUST 1

The 2025 PUBG MOBILE WORLD CUP at ESPORTS WORLD CUP reaches its ultimate stage ‚Äî the Grand Finals begin today in Riyadh! Best of the best will gather to compete, only one will raise to crown. But there‚Äôs a twist ‚Äî will the champion be decided by the SMASH RULE?

After days of fierce competition, the top 16 PUBG MOBILE teams on the globe have secured their place in this final stage ‚Äî chasing glory, legacy, and a share of the $3,000,000 prize pool. This is the moment every team has been grinding for. The best from the Group Stage and the survivors of the Survival Stage now go head-to-head in the most intense showdown of the year. Three days, SMASH RULE, and one champion.

The journey peaks here ‚Äî but only one team will lift the trophy and etch their name into PUBG MOBILE history. Let the Grand Finals begin.

üî• How does SMASH RULE work? 
After Day 2 of Grand Finals, the Match Point Threshold will be set to the #1 ranked team‚Äôs points +10. Any team that hits this must then win a later match to claim the trophy in the last day of Grand Finals‚Äîwinning the same match where they reach the threshold doesn‚Äôt bring the championship. If no team secures the title via SMASH Rule by Match 18, the team with the highest total points wins under standard rules.

üî• Why You Can‚Äôt Miss 2025 PMWC at EWC:
- The top 16 teams on one stage ‚Äî no second chances!
- Every match counts in the race for the championship!
- Witness PUBG MOBILE history in the making!
- Explosive SMASH RULE format ‚Äî pressure-packed, winner-takes-all action!

snippet.description:
#cricketlive #cricketmatch #indvsseng 

INDIA vs ENGLAND, Day 2 Live Commentary  | Live Cricket Match Today | IND vs ENG Live | Session 2

INDIA VS ENGALND Test 5 Day 1 Preview :


What a day of Test match cricket we have seen at the Kennington Oval! Everyone called it a bowling day earlier, and it turned out to be one. Credit to Karun Nair for the way he fought despite getting into the middle in a tough situation. He has made the most of the opportunities given by cricket and is battling hard to keep India in the hunt, playing one of the pivotal innings of his career.   

Overcast, gloomy conditions and a greenish pitch. With rain around, the next thing you hope is not to lose the toss. India weren‚Äôt having a great time with the toss. They lost 15th toss in a row, and Shubman Gill had no other option than batting first in challenging conditions. Both teams made four changes, with England using a four-seam attack, while India having only three pacers in the tank. The hosts didn‚Äôt have the enforcer Ben Stokes, but they had enough venom in their bowling attack to dismantle the tourists, on the toughest batting pitch in this series, despite the Asian side playing an extra batter. 

 Karun Nair scored a fighting fifty as India reached 204 for 6 at Stumps on Day 1 of the fifth and final Test against England at Kennington Oval, London. Sai Sudharsan too helped India's cause with a gritty knock of 38 but rest of the Indian batters failed to play noticeable knocks under the overcast conditions that saw the England pacers dominate. Gus Atkinson and Josh Tongue picked two wickets apiece while Chris Woakes scalped one. Due to rain interruptions, only 64 overs of play was possible on the opening day after England's stand-in captain Ollie Pope won the toss and opted to bowl first. Karun Nair (52 not out) and Washington Sundar (19 not out) were in the middle for India when umpires called off the day. England find themselves in a bit of trouble as Chris Woakes got injured in the 57th over. He fears a shoulder dislocation

India (Probable XI): Yashasvi Jaiswal, KL Rahul, B Sai Sudharsan, Shubman Gill (c), Ravindra Jadeja, Dhruv Jurel (wk), Washington Sundar, Shardul Thakur/Arshdeep Singh, Akash Deep, Mohammed Siraj, Jasprit Bumrah/Prasidh Krishna


England Playing XI: Zak Crawley, Ben Duckett, Ollie Pope (c), Joe Root, Harry Brook, Jacob Bethell, Jamie Smith (wk), Jamie Overton, Chris Woakes, Gus Atkinson, Josh Tongue

localized.title: INDIA vs ENGLAND, Day 2 Live Commentary  | Live Cricket Match Today | IND vs ENG Live | Session 2
localized.description:
#cricketlive #cricketmatch #indvsseng 

INDIA vs ENGLAND, Day 2 Live Commentary  | Live Cricket Match Today | IND vs ENG Live | Session 2

INDIA VS ENGALND Test 5 Day 1 Preview :


What a day of Test match cricket we have seen at the Kennington Oval! Everyone called it a bowling day earlier, and it turned out to be one. Credit to Karun Nair for the way he fought despite getting into the middle in a tough situation. He has made the most of the opportunities given by cricket and is battling hard to keep India in the hunt, playing one of the pivotal innings of his career.   

Overcast, gloomy conditions and a greenish pitch. With rain around, the next thing you hope is not to lose the toss. India weren‚Äôt having a great time with the toss. They lost 15th toss in a row, and Shubman Gill had no other option than batting first in challenging conditions. Both teams made four changes, with England using a four-seam attack, while India having only three pacers in the tank. The hosts didn‚Äôt have the enforcer Ben Stokes, but they had enough venom in their bowling attack to dismantle the tourists, on the toughest batting pitch in this series, despite the Asian side playing an extra batter. 

 Karun Nair scored a fighting fifty as India reached 204 for 6 at Stumps on Day 1 of the fifth and final Test against England at Kennington Oval, London. Sai Sudharsan too helped India's cause with a gritty knock of 38 but rest of the Indian batters failed to play noticeable knocks under the overcast conditions that saw the England pacers dominate. Gus Atkinson and Josh Tongue picked two wickets apiece while Chris Woakes scalped one. Due to rain interruptions, only 64 overs of play was possible on the opening day after England's stand-in captain Ollie Pope won the toss and opted to bowl first. Karun Nair (52 not out) and Washington Sundar (19 not out) were in the middle for India when umpires called off the day. England find themselves in a bit of trouble as Chris Woakes got injured in the 57th over. He fears a shoulder dislocation

India (Probable XI): Yashasvi Jaiswal, KL Rahul, B Sai Sudharsan, Shubman Gill (c), Ravindra Jadeja, Dhruv Jurel (wk), Washington Sundar, Shardul Thakur/Arshdeep Singh, Akash Deep, Mohammed Siraj, Jasprit Bumrah/Prasidh Krishna


England Playing XI: Zak Crawley, Ben Duckett, Ollie Pope (c), Joe Root, Harry Brook, Jacob Bethell, Jamie Smith (wk), Jamie Overton, Chris Woakes, Gus Atkinson, Josh Tongue

snippet.title: Grand Finale : Magnus vs Firouzja | Fight for 3rd Place : Arjun vs Hikaru | Hindi commentary
snippet.description:
The E-sports world cup 2025 begins on 29th July and goes on until 1st of August 2025. It's a 16-player event with some of the biggest names in the world of chess! 

The commentary will be in Hinglish. Watch on Sony Liv without 7 minutes delay: https://www.sonyliv.com/live-sport/e-sports-world-cup-2025-1790006658/esports-chess-at-ewc-25-quarter-finals-semi-finals-31-jul-2025-1090485747?watch=true

Let's try and understand the format:
16 players are segregated in group of 4 players. So there are 4 groups in all. The time control is 10+0. 
On day 1 we had 4 players who topped the 4 groups and will have a rest day on 30th of July 2025.

The players who topped are: 
A group - Levon Aronian
B group - Arjun Erigaisi
C group - Alireza Firouzja
D group - Magnus Carlsen

On day 2 we had 4 more players who joined them:
A group - Ian Nepomniachtchi
B group - Nihal Sarin
C group - Hikaru Nakamura
D group - Nodirbek Abdusattorov

Day 3 was time for Quarter Finals and Semi Finals:
QF:
Arjun Erigaisi beat Ian Nepomniachtchi
Nodirbek Abdusattorov lost to Alireza Firouzja
Magnus Carlsen beat Nihal Sarin
Hikaru Nakamura beat Levon Aronian

SF: 
Arjun Erigaisi lost to Alireza Firouzja
Magnus Carlsen beat Hikaru Nakamura

Today in the finals we will see Magnus Carlsen taking on Alireza Firouzja and Arjun Erigaisi playing against Hikaru Nakamura

The format will be best of 3 sets.

Articles on ChessBase India by Shahid Ahmed:
Day 1: https://chessbase.in/news/Esports-World-Cup-2025-Main-Event-Day-1-report
Day 2: https://chessbase.in/news/Esports-World-Cup-2025-Main-Event-Day-2-report
Day 3: https://chessbase.in/news/Esports-World-Cup-2025-Main-Event-Day-3-report

About The Game
Project Castaway is a survival crafting title set in the Pacific Ocean. Live the life of a stranded castaway, with only yourself - and the island's inhabitants - for company! Sail the ocean, hunt, explore unique islands and gather resources as you fight for survival
Embark on the life of a true castaway - stranded on a deserted island, with just yourself for company. Scavenge or hunt for food, traverse from island to island and be carefully construct rafts & shelters for when the night comes - it can get awfully cold on these islands...
Being stranded has some upsides, at least. Explore beautiful Pacific landscapes. Swim through shimmering blue water to stand upon golden sands as waves crash against your feet. When the weather turns, take cover under palm trees as the rain pelts the ocean - and listen to the thunder crash overhead.
If you enjoyed games like Stranded Deep, Sunkenland, or Raft, then Project Castaway will feel right at home! From underwater exploration to intense survival challenges, this game blends oceanic survival with tropical adventure, making every moment unpredictable and thrilling.
Game: Project Castaway
Platform: PC
Language: Malayalam
